
# CORA MANUAL
# How to build on linux
# Author: Tobias Ladner
# Date: 25-September-2023

# first remove all intermediate LaTeX output files
rm *.aux *.log *.dvi *.ps *.bbl *.blg *.out *.toc

# consider deleting converted eps figures and externalized tikz figures
# Important: These can take a while to re-generate (<30 minutes).
# After they are re-generated, the compilation should be much faster (<20 seconds)*.
# rm ./figures/*-eps-converted-to.pdf
# rm -r ./figures/externalize

# run pdflatex
pdflatex CoraManual --shell-escape

# run bibtex
bibtex CoraManual

# run pdflatex twice
pdflatex CoraManual --shell-escape
pdflatex CoraManual --shell-escape

# from now on, a single pdflatex call should be sufficient to see updates


# ---
# * see also the \includeonly command in CoraManual.tex to reduce compile while working on a single section
